# End-to-End Decision Flow

Every workflow follows the same cognitive pipeline.

1. Perceive information.
2. Understand the business meaning.
3. Retrieve enterprise knowledge.
4. Retrieve company memory.
5. Resolve business context.
6. Apply deterministic rules.
7. Generate multiple hypotheses.
8. Evaluate evidence.
9. Estimate confidence.
10. Build an execution plan.
11. Execute safely.
12. Reflect on the outcome.
13. Learn.
14. Update organisational knowledge.

The workflow is identical regardless of whether the input is:

- invoice;
- bank transaction;
- contract;
- email;
- purchase order;
- tax declaration;
- user request.

---

# Enterprise Knowledge Universe (EKU)

The Enterprise Knowledge Universe represents everything Numera knows about a company.

It contains:

- entities;
- relationships;
- business events;
- memories;
- accounting rules;
- user preferences;
- historical decisions;
- confidence values;
- contextual information.

The EKU is the persistent intelligence of the company.

Agents never own knowledge.

They consult and update the EKU.

